--- orderflow_services/runbook_latency_contract_p411_v1.md	1970-01-01 00:00:00.000000000 +0000
+++ orderflow_services/runbook_latency_contract_p411_v1.md	2026-03-08 11:58:37.330886290 +0000
@@ -0,0 +1,69 @@
+# P4.11 — latency-contract approval freshness and stale-request invalidation
+
+P4.11 tightens P4.10 so prepared / approved dual-control requests cannot stay usable forever.
+
+## Goal
+
+A long deploy-lint silence override request now has two independent freshness windows:
+
+- `LATENCY_CONTRACT_DEPLOY_LINT_SILENCE_APPROVAL_PREPARED_FRESHNESS_S`
+- `LATENCY_CONTRACT_DEPLOY_LINT_SILENCE_APPROVAL_APPROVED_FRESHNESS_S`
+
+If a request stays in `prepared` too long, it becomes `expired` automatically.
+
+If a request stays in `approved` too long without being consumed by the requester, it becomes `cancelled` automatically.
+
+This prevents reuse of stale approvals after conditions have already changed.
+
+## New env
+
+- `LATENCY_CONTRACT_DEPLOY_LINT_SILENCE_APPROVAL_PREPARED_FRESHNESS_S`
+- `LATENCY_CONTRACT_DEPLOY_LINT_SILENCE_APPROVAL_APPROVED_FRESHNESS_S`
+
+Suggested initial defaults:
+
+- prepared freshness: `7200`
+- approved freshness: `1800`
+
+## State transitions
+
+- `prepared -> approved -> consumed`
+- `prepared -> expired`
+- `approved -> cancelled`
+
+Freshness transitions are applied automatically by:
+
+- `status`
+- `ack`
+- exporter reads of latest approval state
+
+## Operational effect
+
+When a stale request is encountered:
+
+- the approval request itself is auto-transitioned to `expired` or `cancelled`
+- an audit event is written
+- final `ack` is denied if it references the stale request
+- operator must create a fresh request and repeat the dual-control workflow
+
+## Audit events
+
+- `latency_deploy_lint_override_approval_expired`
+- `latency_deploy_lint_override_approval_cancelled`
+
+## Metrics
+
+- `latency_contract_deploy_lint_silence_approval_expired{purpose}`
+- `latency_contract_deploy_lint_silence_approval_cancelled{purpose}`
+- `latency_contract_deploy_lint_silence_approval_freshness_remaining_seconds{purpose}`
+- `latency_contract_deploy_lint_summary_dual_control_expired_gate_active_total`
+- `latency_contract_deploy_lint_summary_dual_control_cancelled_gate_active_total`
+
+## Example recovery path
+
+1. operator prepares override
+2. second operator approves
+3. if requester does not consume in time and request is auto-cancelled:
+   - prepare again
+   - approve again
+   - perform final `ack` again with the new `request_id`
